DECLARATION OF INTENT

FOR THE ESTABLISHMENT OF FRENCH-SWEDISH LONG-TERM COOPERATION IN THE

NUCLEAR ENERGY RESEARCH AREA

BETWEEN

THE MINISTER OF HIGHER EDUCATION AND RESEARCH OF THE FRENCH REPUBLIC

AND

THE MINISTER FOR EDUCATION OF THE KINGDOM OF SWEDEN

The Minister of Higher Education and Research of the French Republic,

Ms. Sylvie RETAILLEAU, of the one part,

And

The Minister for Education of the Kingdom of Sweden, Mr. Mats PERSSON, of the other part,

Hereinafter referred to collectively as "the Signatories" and individually as a "Signatory";

RECALLING the French-Swedish strategic innovation partnership for sustainable, digital and resilient societies signed by the President of the French Republic and the Prime Minister of the Kingdom of

Sweden in Stockholm on 30 January 2024;

RECALLING the decision taken jointly by the President of the French Republic and the Prime Minister of the Kingdom of Sweden, in Paris on 3 January 2023, to give civil nuclear cooperation between the signatories an important role in the strategic bilateral relationship;

RECALLING the Declaration of Intent for the establishment of long-term cooperation in the nuclear energy sector signed by the Minister for Energy Transition of the French Republic and the Minister for

Climate and Enterprise of the Kingdom of Sweden on 19 December 2023;

CONSIDERING that France and Sweden, two leading countries in the field of nuclear energy, have recently announced ambitious investments that also involve challenges in terms of research, expertise, nuclear safety, radiation protection, innovation and skills mobilisation;

CONSIDERING the benefit of sharing expertise between the French and Swedish research stakeholders in the field of nuclear energy;

DECLARING their intent to establish a framework for the promotion of scientific and technological cooperation between the Signatories in the nuclear energy research area, as part of the implementation of the Declaration of Intent for the establishment of long-term cooperation in the nuclear energy sector signed by the Minister for Energy Transition of the French Republic and the

Minister for Climate and Enterprise of the Kingdom of Sweden on 19 December 2023;

